CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 18, 1959, pg. A16, reads: "In Saturday Marriage - Mr. and Mrs. W. P. Young were married Saturday in Pittsburgh at the home of the bride's brother, Earl Brooks. The bride is the former Wilnette Brooks Jones, popular Pittsburgher, and a member of the Gay Northeasterners.  Mr. Young is employed in personnel department of Lockhart Steel Company.  The Rev. J. A. Williams performed the ritual, with just the immediate families in attendance. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Bride Wilnette Brooks Jones Young wearing dark suit, light colored gloves, and flowers with short veil, and groom William P. Young wearing carnation and dark suit, posed seated in home of Earl Brooks
